name: micro-services-tutorial
description: This project demonstrates the principles of microservices architecture, utilizing Spring Boot for backend services. It includes user and role management services, integrated with Eureka for service discovery and Zipkin for distributed tracing. Perfect for learning how to build scalable and maintainable applications!.

name: rails_microservices
description: Rails and React microservices application. The application contains authentication features and well as product ordering, stock inventory, viewing orders etc. The services communicate with each other via HTTP APIs, and an API Gateway is used to route requests to the correct services.

name: parking-nest-microservices
description: This project demonstrates a microservices architecture using NestJS, Prisma, RabbitMQ, and SQLite. The application consists of several independent services that communicate through a message bus (RabbitMQ).
